	abstract = {A battery of tests with variables hypothesized to reflect right hemisphere functions was administered to two groups of primary school age disadvantaged subjects. One group demonstrated auditory language deficits and the second group demonstrated left side of the body dysfunction (LSBD). Variables other than unilateral sensorimotor factors associated with the LSBD group were deficts in comprehension, nonverbal expression of creative thinking, and spatial visualization, as well as behavior characterized by impatience, disrespect, irrelevant responsiveness, placing external blame, and classroom disturbance.},
